      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KALKADOON DREAMING (4) kicked off in this region with back-to-back wins earlier in the year and could be close to another success after a second last time out, beaten 3 metres at Coolamon. Could take out a race like this. JANIE BLU (8) is a capable mare who has charged yards since last seen five-and-a-half months ago. Draws wide but she is yet to be beaten in two fresh attempts and should be ready to go off a nice trial. ALWAYS BE BRENDAN (2) didn't do a bad job when fifth from wider at Coolamon last time out and came from this barrier to win at Goulburn three back. ROCK THE NATION NZ (7) draws wide but should be at his peak at the fourth run back from a spell and has yet to miss the top-four this time in.",
